text: Yeah, I would say that the big notable change in policy was with respect to the balance sheet management. They are now going to roll off a smaller portion of their portfolio every month. So in treasury world, they are going to reduce their roll off from 60 billion per month to about 25 billion per month starting on June 1. And so that is a pretty big deal in the sense that the Fed is anticipating that eventually they will need to stop the balance sheet runoff.
